.TH HSH 1 "August 2025" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
Interactive mode:
.B ./hsh
.br
Non-interactive mode:
.B echo "command" | ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C.

It provides a minimal shell environment where users can type
commands, run programs from the system PATH, and use built-in
commands such as
.B exit
and
.B env .

The shell runs in two modes:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive mode: displays a prompt and waits for user input.
.IP \(bu 2
Non-interactive mode: reads commands from standard input.
.RE

.SH REQUIREMENTS
The shell was developed and tested on:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Ubuntu 20.04 LTS
.IP \(bu 2
GCC with options:
\fBgcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh\fR
.RE

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.

.SH USAGE
Example interactive session:
.PP
.EX
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ pwd
$ env
$ exit
.EE

Example non-interact
.EX
#!/bin/sh
echo "Current date:"
date
echo "Files in current directory:"
ls -l
.EE

